article.headline: Hartford 63, Cornell 61
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Joe Zeglinski had 18 points to lead Hartford in a 63-61 win over Cornell Tuesday night. Hartford erased a 10-point deficit in the final 3:24 for the come back. Bo Taylor, who scored 15 for Hartford, started the rally with a pair of free throws. After Hartford (2-3) forced a Cornell (3-3) turnover, Rich Baker scored a three-pointer to cut the deficit in half. Hartford took its first lead of the second half with 49 seconds to play when Taylor scored to go up 62-60. The first half was close, featuring nine ties and five lead changes. Ryan Wittman led Cornell with 22 points. Louis Dale contributed 15. Cornell finished with a 46.8 percent shooting average from the floor. Hartford shot 39.1 percent.
